sections.History:
===[[Season 4]]===

[[Jaime Lannister]] and [[Meryn Trant]] plan security for the [[Purple Wedding|royal wedding]] in the White Sword Tower. King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] reads about the great deeds of [[Arthur Dayne]] and [[Duncan the Tall]] in ''[[The Book of Brothers]]''. He finds Jaime's entry to be very short and sarcastically says Jaime's great deeds are not in the book.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Two Swords]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

While in the Tower, [[Brienne of Tarth]] reads Jaime's entry in the Book of Brothers. Shortly after, Jaime gives Brienne his [[Oathkeeper (sword)|Valyrian steel sword]], a new set of armor, and the mission to locate [[Sansa Stark]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[Cersei Lannister]] confesses her incest with her brother [[Jaime]] to her father [[Tywin]]. She then finds Jaime reading ''The Book of Brothers'' in the Tower, seduces him, and they have sex in the tower.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
